	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=86947><span id=Guru>Annheiser</span></a><br><b><span id=Guru>Guru</span></b><br><span id=notbold>170 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Clickable haste gives you an icon, while worn haste doesn't. That's how you can tell if they stack or don't stack. If I were you I'd start saving for an alternative worn haste item (the swiftblade does too little damage), rather then pursue a clickable haste item to complement your swiftblade. I can't think of anything off the top of my head that you can click for haste (Monks, Rangers, Bards get one) and is usable by a warrior.</p>&nbsp;<br>**********************************<br>"<span style='color: red;'>Man who goes to bed with itchy bum, wakes with smelly fingers.</span style='color: red;'>"</td></td></tr>
